.TH "tb_nvm_write_buf" 9 "tb_nvm_write_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_nvm_write_buf \- Write data to @nvm buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tb_nvm_write_buf
.BI "(struct tb_nvm *nvm "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "void *val "  ","
.BI "size_t bytes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nvm" 12
NVM structure
.IP "offset" 12
Offset where to write the data
.IP "val" 12
Data buffer to write
.IP "bytes" 12
Number of bytes to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Helper function to cache the new NVM image before it is actually
written to the flash. Copies \fIbytes\fP from \fIval\fP to \fInvm->buf\fP starting
from \fIoffset\fP.
